The Southern Oasis is the fortified hinge between oasis civil life and pyramid frontier risk.
Local proverb: "North records; south buries."

Sits at a secondary fracture of the Deepwell Confluence. Never the seat of the Water Court or hub of the charter road network.
From the beginning it was a relay station where the Great Oasis's administrative reach thinned to local improvisation.

The Bastion Wardens, a militarized water-control authority, ration under permanent emergency doctrine.
After the Great Oasis refused to enforce the Twin Basin Compact's emergency water-sharing provisions, the Southern Oasis concluded no external authority would save it.

The settlement processes what the pyramids produce: casualties, disputed relics, broken expeditions.
The Mortuary Circle handles the dead as civic function. The Bazaar Syndics authenticate and tax artifacts with provenance chains trusted across the oasis network.

Expedition convoys are hardened here. Load distribution, casualty drills, and thermal staging protocols are mandatory before departure.
The Lantern Causeway markers preserve Keeper-era distance-toll glyphs.

Springs have diminished faster than the Great Oasis since the Ninth Meridian failure.
Ground tremors propagate from the Southern Pyramid's depths. Locals attribute them to the Moon Sovereign stirring.
